==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entertainer
<hw>En`ter*tain"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who entertains; a host.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>one who amuses people, such as a singer, dancer,
comedian, magician, etc., especially one who does so as a
profession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entertaining</ent>⟦br⟧
